        "created_at": "2020-12-07T20:48:45.973Z",
        "cooked": "<p>Currently, when you are viewing a chat in a bubble and tap on an image, the image viewer opens as a ‚Äúfull‚Äù app <em>behind</em> the bubble, which means you then have to close the bubble in order to view the image. Instead of doing this, the image viewer should open inside the bubble itself. This is more convenient, and consistent with the intention of bubbles, as bubbles are typically used because you don‚Äôt want to bring another app fully into the foreground. I‚Äôm not sure how the majority of other apps handle this, but Facebook Messenger does it this way, so there is precedent for it.</p>\n<p>This was originally posted under support, but it seems the behavior is likely intentional, so it has been updated as a feature request. Original post:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>Continuing the discussion from <a href=\"https://community.signalusers.org/t/beta-feedback-for-the-upcoming-android-5-0-release/18811/36\">Beta feedback for the upcoming Android 5.0 release</a>:</p>\n<aside class=\"quote no-group\" data-username=\"justlurking\" data-post=\"36\" data-topic=\"18811\">\n<div class=\"title\">\n<div class=\"quote-controls\"></div>\n<img loading=\"lazy\" alt=\"\" width=\"24\" height=\"24\" src=\"https://community.signalusers.org/user_avatar/community.signalusers.org/justlurking/48/2838_2.png\" class=\"avatar\"><a href=\"https://community.signalusers.org/t/beta-feedback-for-the-upcoming-android-5-0-release/18811/36\">Beta feedback for the upcoming Android 5.0 release</a></div>\n<blockquote>\n<p>If I find myself with the Signal app open (at the list of conversations) and also with a Signal bubble floating, if I open an image from within the Signal bubble, it opens behind the bubble and I need to tap outside the bubble in order to close the bubble and view the image.</p>\n</blockquote>\n</aside>\n<p>I can confirm this issue. It is present in the current production release (4.79.3), so not a 5.0 beta issue. I don‚Äôt have access to GitHub at the moment, but wanted to create a thread here to ensure awareness of it.</p>\n</blockquote>",
        "post_number": 1,
        "post_type": 1,
        "posts_count": 4,
